    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="904"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d904">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2665.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Mexican Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Memorandum—Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>The Secretary of State presents his compliments to his excellency the Mexican
                    Ambassador, and has the honor to acknowledge the receipt of his note No. 799,
                    dated December 30, 1911,<note n="1" xml:id="d904fn1">See <ref
                            target="frus1911#pg_525">For. Rel., 1911, p. 525</ref>. This is the note
                        referred to in the communication to the Attorney General above.</note>
                    requesting the good offices of the Department of State to cause the local and
                    Federal authorities of Arizona to tighten the vigilance they have been
                    instructed to maintain for the observance of the neutrality statutes of the
                    United States, and stating that recent reports to the Mexican Government
                    indicate that both in Arizona and in California adherents of or sympathizers
                    with the Flores Magón faction constitute a disturbing element, ever ready to
                    cover up or to support a movement against the Mexican Government.</p>
                <p>The Department of State has taken pleasure in transmitting to the Attorney
                    General for such action, if any, as he may see fit to take thereon, a copy of
                    the translation of the Mexican Embassy’s note under acknowledgment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 4, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
